verse_part: and from walking up and down
and from walking up and down
for they had made an appointment
did I [not] give up the ghost
to him that is in misery,
do set themselves in array against me.
the thing that I long for!
of him that hath seen me
and thou shalt seek me in the morning,
and he have cast them away
it shall also prove me perverse.
Oh that I had given up the ghost,
of him that is at ease.
and he maketh them to stagger
and it should be your wisdom.
with me? for now, if I hold my tongue,
I shall give up the ghost.
and that the tender branch thereof
that thou wouldest keep me secret,
And thou hast filled me with wrinkles,
but he hath broken me asunder:
yea, he shall be chased away
and he shall vomit them up again:
is cut off in the midst?
they are taken out of the way
and he that riseth up against me
and as a storm hurleth him
to the roof of their mouth.
of him that was ready to perish
for him that was in trouble?
he was brought up with me,
and by reason of his highness
would I go near unto him.
Then he is gracious unto him,
and he will be favourable unto him:
it is meet to be said
Even so would he have removed
and that which should be set
for I will demand of thee,
of him that layeth at him
they that had been of his acquaintance
